Normalization uncertainty less 0.5%.
GELINA, 150 MeV Geel pulsed electron
linear accelerator, Electron burst width 1 nanosec,
repetition rate 100 Hz,
Initial neutrons produced by (gamma,n) and
(gamma,fis) reactions induced via Bremsstrahlung
from the electron beam hitting a rotating uranium
target, which was cooled by mercury.
Fast neutron from the target moderated to a
white spectrum by water contained in beryllium
canning of 4.0cm thick walls situated above uranium
target
.White Neutron Source. The neutron energy is derived
from the measured time-of-flight using expression -
--EN(eV)=(72.298*L/TOF)**2 with L=26.443 m and TOF
in microseconds. Cd overlap filter, gamma flash was
reduced by 5 mm Pb, background points were determined
with black resonance technique using Cd, Au, and Co
filters. The background was deduced from a fit of the
background points with a power function using AGS.
GELINA Flight path number 2; angle of the flight
path with respect to the electron beam is 279 degree.
